[normal]Once again, I was concerned to find that the Agency had a backlog of cases amounting to 14,000 requests from applicants to re-consider decisions to refuse them further leave to remain. This had been growing by approxi
[normal]mately 700 cases a month. In addition, there were a further 2,100 cases where people were awaiting an initial decision on their application for further leave to remain. Some dated back nearly a decade. This is completely unacceptable…
